Child Application

Child application is a downloadable application which is available over internet in the form of zip file and rendered in a fragment. The child application is self-contained and should be complete as the application rendered as child application do not depend on main application assets for rendering but only the shared the native code required to execute the application.

Development

The development of child application is as follows:

Install Plugins

Install the following plugin in main application which helps to download zip file into local file system:

cordova plugin add https://github.com/AsheraCordova/cordova-plugin-file-downloader.git

Host Child Application

The main application should host the child application in fragment using the namespace and rootDirectory as shown below: 

<fragment
    android:id="@+id/nav_host_fragment_container"
	android:name="androidx.navigation.fragment.NavHostFragment"
	rootDirectory="cordova.file.persistent/CityApp"
	namespace="CityApp"
	navGraph="navigation/nav_graph_child"
	android:layout_width="match_parent"
	android:layout_height="match_parent"></fragment>
The above code loads the child application in the main application into javascript module index_lite.js into namespace CityApp and displays the content of the zip file which has been unzipped at the location "cordova.file.persistent/CityApp""

Sample fragment with a progressbar:
<layout xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"

Backing fragment which downloads the zip file:
//start - import
import { ProgressBar } from './android/widget/ProgressBarImpl';

import { TextView } from './android/widget/TextViewImpl';

//end - import
import { Fragment, Inject } from './app/Fragment';
import { NavController, InjectController } from './navigation/NavController';
import { ScopedObject } from './app/ScopedObject';
declare var downloader: any;
import FragmentFactory from './FragmentFactory';
//start - className
export default class ProgressdialogCityApp extends Fragment
//end - className
{
    //start - body
    @InjectController({})
    navController!: NavController;
    @Inject({ id: "@+id/progress" })

    private progress!: ProgressBar;
    @Inject({ id: "@+id/progressText" })

    private progressText!: TextView;


    async goToPreviousScreen() {
        await this.navController.reset().popBackStack().executeCommand();
    }
    //end - body
    async onCreate() {
        let baseUrl = "your_base_url";
    	let namespace = "your_namespace";
    
        downloader.init({ folder: namespace, unzip: true });

        let downloadProgress = async (event: any) => {
            let data: any = event.data;
            console.log(JSON.stringify(data));
            this.progress.setProgress(data[0]);
            this.progressText.setText(data[0] + "");
            await this.executeCommand(this.progress, this.progressText);
        };

        let gotFolder = (event: any) => {
            var data = event.data;
            //console.log(JSON.stringify(data));
        };

        let unzipFileEntry = async (event: any) => {
            const url = URL.createObjectURL(event.data.file);
            let nativeUrl = event.data.targetFileEntry.toNativeURL();
            nativeUrl = nativeUrl.substring(nativeUrl.indexOf("persistent/"));
            localStorage.setItem(nativeUrl, url);
            if (nativeUrl.endsWith(".9.png") || nativeUrl.endsWith("_9.png")) {
                const img: any = await this.loadImage(url);
                document.body.appendChild(img);  // or set it elsewhere
                console.log(nativeUrl + " image loaded" + url);
            }

            if (nativeUrl.endsWith("ttf") || nativeUrl.endsWith("otf")) {
                const key = nativeUrl.substring(nativeUrl.lastIndexOf('/') + 1).replaceAll('/', '_').replaceAll(' ', '_').replaceAll('%20', '_').replaceAll('.', '_');
                console.log(key + "font loaded");
                await this.loadFont(key, localStorage.getItem(nativeUrl));
            }

            if (nativeUrl.endsWith(".properties") || nativeUrl.endsWith(".xml") || nativeUrl.endsWith(".css")) {
                const text = await this.readTextFromEntry(event.data.targetFileEntry);
                localStorage.setItem(nativeUrl, text as string);
            }
        };

        let successCallBack = async () => {
            try {
                let js = await this.readCdvDataAsString("cordova.file.persistent/CityApp/www/js/index_lite.js");
                const blob = new Blob([js], { type: 'text/javascript' });
                let blobURL;

                if (js.startsWith("blob:")) {
                    blobURL = js;
                } else {
                    const blob = new Blob([js], { type: 'text/javascript' });
                    blobURL = URL.createObjectURL(blob);
                }

                let module: any;
                try {
                    module = await import(/* webpackIgnore: true */ blobURL);
                } catch (e) {
                    console.error("Error loading module:", e);
                    blobURL = `${baseUrl}/city_app/index_lite.js`;
                    try {
                        module = await import(/* webpackIgnore: true */ blobURL);
                    } catch (e) {
                        console.error("Error loading module:", e);
                        throw e;
                    }
                }

                FragmentFactory.registerFragmentMapper('CityApp', module.fragmentMapper);
                await new module.AppLoader().loadApp("cordova.file.persistent/CityApp");
                this.removeListeners(downloadProgress, gotFolder, failureCallBack, successCallBack, unzipFileEntry);
                this.navController.closeDialog().executeCommand();
            } catch (e) {
                this.removeListeners(downloadProgress, gotFolder, failureCallBack, successCallBack, unzipFileEntry);
                await this.navController.closeDialog().executeCommand();
                alert(e + " Error in loading app. Please try again.");
            }
        };

        let failureCallBack = () => {
            this.removeListeners(downloadProgress, gotFolder, failureCallBack, successCallBack, unzipFileEntry);
            this.navController.closeDialog().executeCommand();
        };

        document.addEventListener("DOWNLOADER_downloadProgress", downloadProgress);
        document.addEventListener("DOWNLOADER_gotFolder", gotFolder);
        document.addEventListener("DOWNLOADER_downloadError", failureCallBack);
        document.addEventListener("UNZIP_fileentry", unzipFileEntry);
        document.addEventListener("DOWNLOADER_unzipSuccess", successCallBack);
        downloader.setDownloadError(failureCallBack);
        downloader.get(`${baseUrl}/city_app.zip`);
    }


    private removeListeners(downloadProgress: (event: any) => any, gotFolder: (event: any) => void, failureCallBack: any, successCallBack: any, unzipFileEntry: any) {
        document.removeEventListener("DOWNLOADER_downloadProgress", downloadProgress);
        document.removeEventListener("DOWNLOADER_gotFolder", gotFolder);
        document.removeEventListener("DOWNLOADER_downloadSuccess", successCallBack);
        document.removeEventListener("DOWNLOADER_unzipSuccess", successCallBack);
        document.removeEventListener("DOWNLOADER_downloadError", failureCallBack);
        document.removeEventListener("UNZIP_fileEntry", unzipFileEntry);
    }

    async loadFont(name: string, url: string | null) {
        // @ts-ignore
        const font = new FontFace(name, `url(${url})`);
        await font.load();             // Wait until font is downloaded and parsed
        (document as any).fonts.add(font);     // Add to document so it can be used
        console.log(`Font ${name} loaded ${url}`);
    }
    loadImage(url: any) {
        return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {
            const img = new Image();
            img.onload = () => resolve(img);     // âœ… resolve with the image element
            img.onerror = (err) => reject(err);  // â�Œ reject on error
            img.src = url;
            img.id = url;
            img.style.visibility = "hidden";
        });
    }

    getFile(fileEntry: any) {
        return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {
            fileEntry.file(resolve, reject);
        });
    }

    // Read File as text
    readFileAsText(file: any) {
        return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {
            const reader = new FileReader();
            reader.onload = () => resolve(reader.result);
            reader.onerror = reject;
            reader.readAsText(file);
        });
    }

    // Usage with async/await
    async readTextFromEntry(fileEntry: any) {
        const file = await this.getFile(fileEntry);
        return await this.readFileAsText(file);
    }

}

Child app development

  • Develop the child application as standalone application using Ashera framework.
  • In the main page of the application, create child fragment which loads a nav_graph_child.xml.
  • Use child fragment for navigation from one page to another. Do not use navController.
  • Use the command npm run generate-platform-js-child to create index_lite.js
  • Append the following string to index_lite.js. 
    export const fragmentMapper = window.__DYNAMIC_MODULE__.fragmentMapper;
export const AppLoader = window.__DYNAMIC_MODULE__.AppLoader;

Create zip file

The structure of zip file is shown below: 

zip file
├──  www/
│   ├── css
│   ├── js
│   │	└── index_lite.js
│   └── img
├── res/
├──	res-ios
├──	resources
├──	res-swt
└──	 res-swt

Use the command npm install archiver to install archiver as dependency in child app.

Code to create archiver.zip by running command "node zip-folder.js" given below: 
#!/usr/bin/env node
/**
 * zip-folder.js
 *
 * Usage:
 *   node zip-folder.js
 *
 */

const fs = require('fs');
const path = require('path');
const archiver = require('archiver');

/**
 * Zip multiple directories into one archive
 * @param {string[]} sourceDirs - list of directories
 * @param {string} outPath - output zip file path
 */
async function zipFolders(sourceDirs, outPath) {
  return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {
    // Prepare output stream (overwrite if exists)
    const output = fs.createWriteStream(outPath);
    const archive = archiver('zip', { zlib: { level: 9 } });

    output.on('close', () => {
      resolve({
        bytes: archive.pointer(),
        outPath,
      });
    });

    archive.on('warning', (err) => {
      if (err.code === 'ENOENT') {
        console.warn('Archiver warning:', err.message);
      } else {
        reject(err);
      }
    });

    archive.on('error', (err) => {
      reject(err);
    });

    archive.pipe(output);

    // Add each directory
    for (const dir of sourceDirs) {
      if (!fs.existsSync(dir) || !fs.statSync(dir).isDirectory()) {
        console.warn(`Skipping invalid directory: ${dir}`);
        continue;
      }
      const baseName = path.basename(dir);
      archive.directory(dir, baseName);
    }

    archive.finalize();
  });
}

// CLI handling
async function main() {
  const zipDirs = ['platforms/android/app/src/main/assets/www', 'platforms/android/app/src/main/res',
  'platforms/android/app/src/main/res-ios', 'platforms/android/app/src/main/res-swt', 
  'platforms/android/app/src/main/resources'];
  const dirs = zipDirs.map((d) => path.resolve(d));

  console.log(`Zipping directories:`);
  dirs.forEach((d) => console.log(' -', d));

  try {
    const res = await zipFolders(dirs, "archiver.zip");
    console.log(`Done — ${res.bytes} bytes written to ${res.outPath}`);
  } catch (err) {
    console.error('Failed to create zip:', err.stack || err);
    process.exit(1);
  }
}

if (require.main === module) main();
